article.description: Dallas Moore scored a career-high 37 points and North Florida rolled to a 109-73 win over Edward Waters on Monday night.
article.headline: Moore pours in 37 as N Florida crushes Edward Waters 109-73
article.linkText: Moore pours in 37 as N Florida crushes Edward Waters 109-73
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Dallas Moore scored a career-high 37 points and North Florida rolled to a 109-73 win over Edward Waters on Monday night. Romelo Banks added 16 points and nine rebounds and his six blocks was one short of the school record for the Osprey (1-1). Moore hit 10 of 13 shots, including 3 of 6 3-pointers and had 29 points in the first half. North Florida shot 61 percent in the first half despite making just 3 of 14 3-pointers and led 60-34. The Osprey finished the game at 51.5 percent and made 33 of 45 free throws. Keith Williams Jr. had 18 points for Edward Waters, a cross-town NAIA school. Edward Waters shot 29 percent but made 26 of 36 free throws. Edward Waters was within nine but North Florida closed the half with a 24-7 run.
